                            The Bride of FidoSpine
                            Echomail Drama Review
                  Douglas Myers  1:270/720  doug@mdtnbbs.com

     If one were to stand with one ear to the Z1C echo and one to the
     BACKBONE echo... and if one were to listen very carefully, then on a
     quiet day one can hear the drama played out by the Stars.  Actually,
     you probably don't need a hearing aid right now as the Northwestern
     Star moves into its ascendancy and the Southern Star threatens to go
     Supernova...

     The latest drama is about the lifeblood of Fidonet... echomail.  It
     opens in a small monastery somewhere in the Southern Star, where
     Brother John is dutifully installing the inscriptions of the new
     Northwestern Star to the Holy Writings.  Brother John is wary,
     though, when he discovers that the new star is supported by a
     FidoSpine rather than the North American Backbone found in all the
     faithful.

     The good Friar is wise to the ways of an ancient people who, as the
     legend goes, thrive on the very lifeblood of Fidonet.  Suspecting
     that Count Bob may not be One Of Us, the monk unveils the Mirror of
     BoFaq... and finds that Count Bob casts no reflection upon it.

     The lastest installment closes on a cliffhanger, as Brother John
     calls upon the OBO Almighty to expose the Count to the light of day
     and drive him forever from the land.  But the Count escapes to the
     darkness of his own castle, revealing that a secret pact has
     actually given him posession of the North American Backbone to be
     forever the Bride of Fidospine.

     Fans of Gothic Apocalypse should find this tale interesting.  We
     at Fidonews give it "two thumbs up" and wait with bated breath for
     the consummation.

