                         NO ZEC NEED APPLY IN ZONE 1

     The Regional Echomail Coordinator's Council has emerged from months
     of secluded deliberations.  Their action on the Zone Coordinator's
     charge to determine the method of election of their chairperson
     is... no action.  The RECC has decided that it doesn't need a ZEC.

     Supporters of this resolution point out that echomail flows just
     fine despite the lack of a ZEC for the recent past.  Pundits point
     out that the same arguement can be applied to the RECC.  In the
     meantime, the RECC waits - ready to spring into inaction - while the
     ZC reviews their resolution to come to no decision.

     And no ZEC need apply...


                              UNREQUESTING ECHOS

     The R13EC has introduced a new variation to the process of adding
     echoes to the North American Backbone.  Normally, an echo is
     elisted, and then the moderator requests addition to the NAB.  If
     two REC's subsequently request the echo for their region, it is then
     carried by the BACKBONE, available to all.

     In an interesting maneuver recently, the R13EC "unrequested" two of
     the echoes under consideration.  It's not clear at this point
     whether this action cancels a "request" or if the action is strictly
     symbolic.  It's not even clear what was wrong with the echos, as the
     R13EC tells us that the original unrequestor has not provided
     further information.

     This looks like a prime candidate for WHAT'S NOT HAPPENING, but just
     in case the idea catches on, here are some other echos for future
     unrequesting:

     CPLUSPLUSPLUS   Assertiveness training for Fidonet Coordinators.
                     Unrequested by programmers everywhere.

     AERHEAD         Aerobic exercises for sinus disorders.  Unrequested
                     by the blonde lobby.

     ECHOLAW         Discussion of the principles of sound propagation in
     FIDONEWS 15-46               Page 6                   16 Nov 1998


                     mountainous terrain.  Unrequested by just about
                     everyone.

